## Data Structure Choice

The optimal solution uses a **doubly-linked list + hash map** combination:

| Structure | Purpose | Why |
|-----------|---------|-----|
| `HashMap<key, Node>` | O(1) key lookup | Direct node access without traversal |
| Doubly-Linked List | O(1) insertion/deletion | Prev pointer eliminates backward search |
| Sentinel nodes (head/tail) | Boundary management | Eliminates null checks on edge operations |

**Why not alternatives?**
- `Array`: O(n) removal/insertion → fails O(1) requirement
- `Singly-linked list`: O(n) deletion without prev pointer
- `Map` alone: No efficient ordering mechanism

