# LRU Cache in TypeScript: A Dance of Memory and Forgetting

Think of an LRU cache as a **bookshelf with limited space** — the books you read most recently stay within reach, while the forgotten ones get donated to make room for new arrivals.

---

## Data Structure Choice: HashMap + Doubly Linked List

The secret lies in **combining two structures**:

- **HashMap** (`Map<K, Node>`) → O(1) lookup by key
- **Doubly Linked List** → O(1) insertion/deletion at any position (given a node reference)

A singly linked list would force O(n) traversal to find a node's predecessor. The double links let us **surgically remove** any node in constant time.

---

## Complete Implementation

```typescript
class LRUNode<K, V> {
  key: K;
  value: V;
  prev: LRUNode<K, V> | null = null;
  next: LRUNode<K, V> | null = null;

  constructor(key: K, value: V) {
    this.key = key;
    this.value = value;
  }
}

class LRUCache<K, V> {
  private capacity: number;
  private map: Map<K, LRUNode<K, V>>;

  // Sentinel nodes: head = oldest (LRU end), tail = newest (MRU end)
  // Using sentinels eliminates null-checks at boundaries
  private head: LRUNode<K, V>; // dummy head
  private tail: LRUNode<K, V>; // dummy tail

  constructor(capacity: number) {
    if (capacity <= 0) {
      throw new RangeError("LRU Cache capacity must be a positive integer.");
    }

    this.capacity = Math.floor(capacity); // guard against floats
    this.map = new Map();

    // Initialize dummy sentinel nodes
    this.head = new LRUNode<K, V>(null as unknown as K, null as unknown as V);
    this.tail = new LRUNode<K, V>(null as unknown as K, null as unknown as V);
    this.head.next = this.tail;
    this.tail.prev = this.head;
  }

  /**
   * Retrieve a value by key.
   * Side effect: marks the node as most-recently-used.
   * Returns undefined if key doesn't exist.
   * Time: O(1)
   */
  get(key: K): V | undefined {
    const node = this.map.get(key);
    if (!node) return undefined;

    // Promote to MRU position
    this.moveToTail(node);
    return node.value;
  }

  /**
   * Insert or update a key-value pair.
   * If at capacity, evicts the least-recently-used entry first.
   * Time: O(1)
   */
  put(key: K, value: V): void {
    if (this.map.has(key)) {
      // Update existing node
      const node = this.map.get(key)!;
      node.value = value;
      this.moveToTail(node);
    } else {
      // Evict LRU if at capacity
      if (this.map.size >= this.capacity) {
        this.evictLRU();
      }

      // Insert new node at MRU position (just before tail sentinel)
      const newNode = new LRUNode(key, value);
      this.insertBeforeTail(newNode);
      this.map.set(key, newNode);
    }
  }

  /**
   * Peek at a value without affecting recency order.
   * Useful for read-only inspection.
   * Time: O(1)
   */
  peek(key: K): V | undefined {
    return this.map.get(key)?.value;
  }

  /**
   * Remove a specific key from the cache.
   * Time: O(1)
   */
  delete(key: K): boolean {
    const node = this.map.get(key);
    if (!node) return false;

    this.removeNode(node);
    this.map.delete(key);
    return true;
  }

  /** Current number of entries. */
  get size(): number {
    return this.map.size;
  }

  /** Check if a key exists (without updating recency). */
  has(key: K): boolean {
    return this.map.has(key);
  }

  /** Clear all entries. */
  clear(): void {
    this.map.clear();
    this.head.next = this.tail;
    this.tail.prev = this.head;
  }

  /**
   * Returns entries from LRU (oldest) to MRU (newest).
   * Useful for debugging / inspection.
   */
  entries(): [K, V][] {
    const result: [K, V][] = [];
    let current = this.head.next;
    while (current !== this.tail) {
      result.push([current!.key, current!.value]);
      current = current!.next;
    }
    return result;
  }

  // ─── Private Helpers ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  /** Detach a node from its current position in the list. */
  private removeNode(node: LRUNode<K, V>): void {
    const prev = node.prev!;
    const next = node.next!;
    prev.next = next;
    next.prev = prev;
    node.prev = null;
    node.next = null;
  }

  /** Insert a detached node just before the tail sentinel (MRU position). */
  private insertBeforeTail(node: LRUNode<K, V>): void {
    const prev = this.tail.prev!;
    prev.next = node;
    node.prev = prev;
    node.next = this.tail;
    this.tail.prev = node;
  }

  /** Move an existing node to the MRU position. */
  private moveToTail(node: LRUNode<K, V>): void {
    this.removeNode(node);
    this.insertBeforeTail(node);
  }

  /** Remove the node just after head sentinel (LRU position) and delete from map. */
  private evictLRU(): void {
    const lruNode = this.head.next;
    if (lruNode === this.tail) return; // cache is empty (shouldn't happen)

    this.removeNode(lruNode!);
    this.map.delete(lruNode!.key);
  }
}
