### Data Structure Choice

Achieving **O(1) for both `get` and `put`** requires two structures working together:

1. **HashMap** (`Map<number, Node>`) — O(1) key lookup to find any node instantly.
2. **Doubly-Linked List** — O(1) node removal and insertion at head/tail (we always know the node pointer from the map, so no traversal needed).

A singly-linked list would require O(n) removal. A plain array/object alone can't reorder in O(1). The combination is the classic solution.

**Layout:** `[head (sentinel)] <-> [most-recently-used] <-> ... <-> [least-recently-used] <-> [tail (sentinel)]`

Sentinel head/tail nodes eliminate null checks on boundary operations.

