# LRU Cache Implementation in TypeScript

## Data Structure Choice

An LRU cache requires **O(1) for both get and put**, which demands two complementary structures:

| Structure | Purpose | Operation |
|-----------|---------|-----------|
| **HashMap** | Key → Node lookup | O(1) access |
| **Doubly Linked List** | Tracks recency order | O(1) insertion/deletion |

A singly linked list won't work because removing an arbitrary node requires O(n) traversal to find its predecessor. The HashMap alone can't track order. Together, they give us exactly what we need.

```
Most Recent                    Least Recent
    ↓                               ↓
[HEAD] ⟺ [Node A] ⟺ [Node B] ⟺ [TAIL]
             ↑           ↑
          HashMap     HashMap
         key → A     key → B
```

